math
Interface Function

All Known Implementing Classes:
Const, Cos, Cube, Divide, Exp, Log, Minus, Multiply, Plus, Quart, Sin, Sqrt, Square, Var
public interface Function

Abstraction/extension of the genotype evaluation traversal. The problem: we need to traverse the entire genotype tree to evaluate every single training case. This is expensive (in running time). Solution: traverse tree once, capture that traversal as a Function, and use that for evaluations. That's the purpose of this interface and all implementations of this interface. A further optimization might be to perform some sort of static analysis to intelligently remove useless/dead subexpressions (such as those which always evaluate to the same value, or don't affect any subsequent evaluations).

Author:
Owen Derby
